# Semgrep false-positive suppressions
#
# The "Path Traversal with Actix" rule fires on any std::fs call whose path
# originates from a function parameter of type PathBuf.  The files listed
# below only use operator-controlled paths (from SPOOLMAN_DATA_FILE env var
# or derived from it) — never user-supplied HTTP input — so these findings
# are false positives.
crates/spoolman-server/src/backup.rs
crates/spoolman-server/src/store.rs
